1
00:00:05,521 --> 00:00:09,378
Ma Kali, what is she doing? 
Indiscriminately killing everyone!

2
00:00:09,687 --> 00:00:12,759
[Kali, Ganesh and Shiva]

3
00:00:13,299 --> 00:00:16,567
We know women 
can get very angry …

4
00:00:16,567 --> 00:00:20,377
[Laughing]

5
00:00:20,377 --> 00:00:26,287
She’s not only killing the demons,
she’s killing her own people.

6
00:00:26,687 --> 00:00:28,819
That’s intense.

7
00:00:28,819 --> 00:00:32,298
So Mahādev, 
he lies before her on the ground

8
00:00:32,298 --> 00:00:34,666
and when she steps on his chest,
she looks down

9
00:00:34,666 --> 00:00:39,901
and she goes like,
“Oops!”

10
00:00:39,901 --> 00:00:42,519
And then she stops.

11
00:00:48,817 --> 00:00:52,243
But it’s mentioned
in Bṛhad-bhāgavatāmṛtam, interestingly,

12
00:00:52,243 --> 00:00:54,046
in that section—
Nārada and Śiva:

13
00:00:54,046 --> 00:00:59,349
Nārada’s praising Śiva,
Śiva’s deflecting all the praise

14
00:01:01,139 --> 00:01:04,656
and saying
what a bad person he is.

15
00:01:04,656 --> 00:01:10,577
Devotees are extraordinary.
Vaiṣṇavam amṛtam Śambu.

16
00:01:10,577 --> 00:01:21,137
He’s saying, “So many times
I fight with Kṛṣṇa and His …”

17
00:01:21,137 --> 00:01:22,659
Sometimes Guru Mahārāj
would say,

18
00:01:22,659 --> 00:01:26,439
“Gaṇesh. Gaṇa Īśa. Gaṇapati.”

19
00:01:26,439 --> 00:01:31,270
He said,
“He’s the leader of the people.”

20
00:01:31,270 --> 00:01:36,217
He said it’s like democracy.
[Laughing]

21
00:01:36,217 --> 00:01:39,647
Leader of the opposition.
So Śiva’s saying,

22
00:01:39,647 --> 00:01:42,216
“We are the leaders 
of the opposition to Kṛṣṇa

23
00:01:42,216 --> 00:01:44,521
in so many instances,”

24
00:01:44,521 --> 00:01:48,122
and he said, “and not only that;
I’m ashamed to say

25
00:01:48,122 --> 00:01:52,658
that I even wanted
to be greater than Kṛṣṇa.

26
00:01:52,658 --> 00:01:55,708
Such a shameless person I am.”

27
00:01:55,708 --> 00:01:57,604
But Sanātan Goswāmī says,

28
00:01:57,604 --> 00:02:00,276
“What he means to say is,

29
00:02:00,276 --> 00:02:03,298
‘Who is greater than Kṛṣṇa?

30
00:02:03,298 --> 00:02:05,283
Who can be considered 
greater than Kṛṣṇa

31
00:02:05,283 --> 00:02:08,480
but the devotees of Kṛṣṇa?’”

32
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:09,937
So it’s his way of saying

33
00:02:09,937 --> 00:02:12,521
“I wanted to be
a devotee of Kṛṣṇa.

34
00:02:12,521 --> 00:02:15,818
That’s my aspiration.”

35
00:02:15,818 --> 00:02:18,448
So very beautiful.
But he’s made that

36
00:02:18,448 --> 00:02:22,359
into something 
that’s self-deprecating.

37
00:02:22,359 --> 00:02:24,687
Anyway, they’re going 
back and forth—

38
00:02:24,687 --> 00:02:29,938
Nārada insisting,
Śiva deflecting, deferring.

39
00:02:29,938 --> 00:02:34,457
But Pārvatī,
she’s listening to all of this,

40
00:02:34,457 --> 00:02:36,685
their conversation,

41
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:39,905
and she’s thinking,

42
00:02:39,905 --> 00:02:44,297
“I don’t hear anything out there 
about the female section!”

43
00:02:44,297 --> 00:02:49,497
[Laughing]

44
00:02:50,977 --> 00:02:55,458
And then she begins to speak,
and it’s very beautiful.

45
00:02:55,458 --> 00:02:57,218
And there Sanātan Goswāmī says,

46
00:02:57,218 --> 00:03:00,127
“Actually, she can give bhakti.

47
00:03:00,127 --> 00:03:01,854
She can give devotion, 
she can liberate,

48
00:03:01,854 --> 00:03:04,854
she can do everything.”

49
00:03:04,854 --> 00:03:09,137
chāyeva yasya bhuvanāni bibharti durgā 
[Bs: 5.44]

50
00:03:09,137 --> 00:03:12,049
The shadow of Hlādinī-śakti.

51
00:03:12,049 --> 00:03:18,138
The shadow representation 
of Rādhārāṇī and Vraja-gopīs.

52
00:03:18,138 --> 00:03:27,187
Saraswatī Ṭhākur says, 
“Durga-devī is a Vraja-gopī in Goloka.”

53
00:03:27,187 --> 00:03:33,812
So of course it’s rare,
but they can.

54
00:03:34,738 --> 00:03:38,338
It’s by the grace of the devotees

55
00:03:38,338 --> 00:03:41,898
that Kṛṣṇa conception is extended.

